# {{.Name}} ({{.Type}})

Manages one macOS setting backed by a `defaults` key.

Use this resource when you want a separate Terraform resource address for one macOS setting. For larger preference sets, use `host_mac_settings`.

## Example Usage

{{ tffile "examples/resources/host_mac_setting/resource.tf" }}

## Value Attributes

Set `value` to a bool, number, string, or list of strings.

## Restart Behavior

When `restart` is omitted, the provider applies built-in restarts for known domains such as Dock, Finder, SystemUIServer menu extras, global preferences, trackpad preferences, and accessibility preferences. Set `restart = []` to disable restarts for a specific setting.

